cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CR 

This paper deals with scene parsing using deep learning methods, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of synthetic data and weak supervision, which are both relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The integration of depth-based adaptation and weak supervision is also relevant to robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper discusses the use of contour-based schemes, which is relevant to cryptography (cs.CR).
